#  Best Practices

- Avoid creating unnecessary objects.
- Remove unused object references.
- Close files, streams, sockets, and database connections.
- Use `StringBuilder` instead of repeated String concatenation.
- Avoid large static collections.
- Use Weak References where appropriate.
- Monitor memory using tools like **VisualVM**, **JConsole**, or **Java Flight Recorder (JFR)**.
- Tune JVM Heap size according to application requirements.

---

#  Heap vs Stack

| Heap Memory | Stack Memory |
|-------------|--------------|
| Stores objects | Stores local variables and method calls |
| Shared among all threads | Thread-specific |
| Managed by Garbage Collector | Automatically released after method execution |
| Larger memory area | Smaller memory area |
| Slower access | Faster access |

