#  Summary

- Java manages memory automatically using the JVM.
- Heap stores objects, while Stack stores method execution data.
- Garbage Collection removes unreachable objects from memory.
- The Heap is divided into Young and Old Generations.
- Understanding JVM memory areas and Garbage Collection is essential for writing efficient Java applications and performing well in interviews.
